<misra_rule>
MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.1 is: A project shall not contain unreachable code.

</misra_rule>
<response format>
Provide your answer with these fields.
- is_rule_violated: whether the rule is violated or not (true/false),
- scenario: a specific violation scenario.
</response format>
<target_code>
Here is the code of parse_options:
```c
static enum MHD_Result
parse_options (struct MHD_Daemon *daemon,
               struct MHD_InterimParams_ *params,
               ...)
{
  va_list ap;
  enum MHD_Result ret;

  va_start (ap, params);
  ret = parse_options_va (daemon,
                          params,
                          ap);
  va_end (ap);
  return ret;
}
```
</target_code>
<target_code>
Here is the code fragment that you need to analyze:
```c
va_end (ap);
```
Focus on the above code fragment and judge whether it violates the rule 2.1 or not.
</target_code>
scenario: No violation in the shown code: va_end(ap) is reachable in the normal control flow. A violation would occur only if parse_options_va is guaranteed not to return (e.g. it is declared noreturn or it always calls exit/abort/longjmp), making the va_end(ap) statement unreachable.
